<dl id="n56128d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56128d">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56128d"> 128(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> divan</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Now he had a short sword of watered steel, which he held so dear that he went not to his father&apos;s <mark>Divan</mark>, except he were girt therewith; and his father used to laugh at him and exclaim, &ldquo;Mahallah! This is a mighty fine sword of thine, O my son! But thou hast not gone down with it to battle nor cut off a head therewith.&rdquo; <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE4" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE4"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 52</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
